	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A mother was killed and her baby seriously injured, when they were hit by a car on the N1 between Beaufort West and Leeu Gamka on Saturday afternoon, Western Cape traffic authorities have confirmed. Traffic chief Kenny Africa said the pedestrian, a 34-year-old Zimbabwean national, had gotten out of a car to cross the road to urinate. She had been carrying the baby on her back. The woman sustained fatal injuries and the baby was seriously hurt when the Nissan – driving in the direction on Beaufort West - hit them, he said. According to eNCA, nearly 20 fatalities have been reported in the province in the last week.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.